default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultI will give a voice to the public, especially victims of crime, and work with other
defaultservices to ensure the safety of the community and effective criminal justice.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultI will take all steps within my power to ensure transparency of my decisions, 
defaultso that I may be properly held to account by the public.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultI will not interfere with the operational independence of police officers.
defaultThis is a very powerful set of requirements and I often use it when explaining the role of the 
defaultCommissioner, not just to external organisations but also to the force and Chief Officers to 
defaultshow that I have to have regard to all those factors which affect crime prevention and 
defaultreduction. Part of this remit, explicitly, is ensuring an 
defaulteffective and efficient defaultcriminal justice 
defaultsystem.
defaultAnother approach which I have taken as the cornerstone of my work are Peel's 9 principles 
defaultfor policing:
default1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe basic mission for which the police exist is to prevent crime and disorder.
default2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe ability of the police to perform their duties is dependent upon the public 
defaultapproval of police actions.
default3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPolice must secure the willing co-operation of the public in voluntary 
defaultobservation of the law to be able to secure and maintain the respect of the 
defaultpublic.
default4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe degree of co-operation of the public that can be secured diminishes 
defaultproportionately to the necessity of the use of physical force.
default5.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPolice seek and preserve public favour not by catering to public opinion, but 
defaultby constantly demonstrating absolute impartial service to the law.
default6.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPolice use physical force to the extent necessary to secure observance of the 
defaultlaw or to restore order only when the exercise of persuasion, advice, and 
defaultwarning is found to be insufficient.
default7.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPolice, at all times, should maintain a relationship with the public that gives 
defaultreality to the historic tradition that the police are the public and the public are 
defaultthe police; the police being only members of the public who are paid to give full-time attention to duties which are incumbent upon every citizen in the 
defaultinterests of community welfare and existence.
default8.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPolice should always direct their action strictly towards their functions, and 
defaultnever appear to usurp the powers of the judiciary.
default9.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe test of police efficiency is the absence of crime and disorder, not the 
defaultvisible evidence of police action in dealing with it
default&#xa0;
defaultAlthough these nine principles have stood the test of time, I believe a 10
defaultth
default principle needs to 
defaultbe added to follow on from this to recognise that perception and reality are not the same. 
defaultWhen the public are bombarded with "bad news stories" it is not surprising that the fear of 
defaultcrime is often greater than the reality. My suggested 10
defaultth
default principle would be:
default"Understand the real levels of crime, not just what is reported, and defaultshare this knowledge with the public to reduce the fear of crime."defaultAs well as the communications challenge this presents, there is a need to understand the 
defaulttrue levels of crime rather than depending just on what is reported to the police. You will be 
defaultaware of the work of Professor Jonathan Shepherd in Cardiff who has worked scientifically 
defaultto help the police and the council to drastically reduce levels of city centre violence through 
defaultanalysis of the experience of victims presenting at A&amp;E.
defaultIn the 1990s police, councillors and media alike knew that violence was random and 
defaultunpredictable in Cardiff City Centre. Police and NHS and others had to wait to see what 
defaulthappened and react. The first results of the analysis of A&amp;E Data showed that this was 
defaultsimply untrue. Violence was concentrated quite disproportionately in a small number of 
defaultlocations. That information led to prophylactic deployment of police, discussions with 
defaultrelevant licensees, better information for all emergency services and a significant drop in 
defaultviolent incidents. Analysis of injuries led to the use of toughened glass and a reduction in the 
defaultseriousness of many offences.
defaultInformation can be anonymised and used to target resources by time and location to prevent 
defaultfurther violence. We are applying that sort of analytic approach to other manifestations of 
defaultviolence and indeed other aspects of crime.
defaultIn these circumstances a focus on evidence (of need and of "what works") is essential to 
defaultidentifying the most efficient course of action and the most effective partnership approach. 
defaultReduction of pressure on partners is itself a tangible benefit, as is the cut in the number of 
defaultvictims and the reduction of public fear and concern. It has to be underpinned by the 
defaultprinciple of strategic agreement and tactical delivery.
defaultAt the core of this approach is a need to identify specific local places of concern with regards 
defaultto incidents of violent crime using injury reports from Accident and Emergency units in 
defaultaddition to recorded incidents and police intelligence. Data on "hotspots" of violent incidents 
defaultenables police deployment to target problem areas and cut offending. Better deployment of 
defaultparamedics, ambulances and other emergency services can cut demand so that fewer people become victims of violent crime, fewer people present at A&amp;E and the injuries 
defaultpresented are less serious.
default&#xa0;
defaultIt is through these approaches and in partnership with agencies and voluntary groups across South Wales that I am trying to develop a co-ordinated, evidence-based approach to crime 
defaultprevention. This is dependent on building relationships and understanding local needs and 
defaultthe local context which needs to be recognised by Ministers, and by the Treasury. 
defaultConsistent local action can change the national scene, but national action is only truly 
defaulteffective if it empowers effective local action.
